                <note rend="inline" type="source">500. A 4e/117: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-10-24T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 24, 1922—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>247. Your telegram 422, October 18, 12 noon.</p>
                <p>The Department authorizes you to accept the Japanese suggestion, assuming it to
                    imply that goods shall be entitled to entry at the old tariff rates if actually
                    shipped for China by December 1st (as indicated in your telegram 403, October 2,
                    4 p.m.), or within two weeks after public notice of assent or acquiescence by
                    all the nations which have participated in the recent tariff revision.</p>
                <p>Advise Department promptly of conclusion arrived at.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
